ORGANIZER;CN="Molina, Javier (NCMI, Clayton)":mailto:Javier.Molina@csiro.au
DESCRIPTION:What to expect\nFor more than a decade the Atlas of Living Aust
 ralia (ALA) has run mainly on self-managed server infrastructure that whil
 e dependable has posed challenges as the ALA has matured and grown.\n\nThi
 s talk introduces the ALA's next-generation platform: a modern\, cloud-nat
 ive foundation built on AWS. Rather than being a single technology next-ge
 n is about the adoption of modern practices and services to allow us to ra
 pidly develop and deliver high quality applications with a lower cost and 
 carbon footprint.\n\nSome of the technologies covered will be our managed 
 Kubernetes cluster\, statically hosted React SPAs\, managed databases and 
 other services. Also\, our automated deployment CICD framework that is use
 d to manage and launch applications as well as underlying platforms.\n\nFi
 nally\, we will look in more detail at a single application\; how it’s d
 eveloped\, deployed and hosted under next-gen.\n\nThis event will be recor
 ded and the recording made available through the Living Atlases slack chan
 nel in the week after the event.\n\nTime and date\nTuesday 16 June 2026  6
 -7pm AEST (8-9am  UTC)\nSee it in your local time zone<https://www.timeand
 date.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?msg=Living+Atlases+Information+Session+
 -+The+ALA+Next-Gen+Platform&iso=20260616T18&p1=152&ah=1>.\n\nHow to join\n
 This is an online event that will be broadcast using MS Teams\, follow the
  links at the bottom to join.\n\nFurther information\nThis event will be r
 ecorded and the recording made available through the Living Atlases slack 
 channel<https://ala.us14.list-manage.com/track/click?u=b238aea31bbd4bd103f
 f7368c&id=4252e0d32e&e=e24f40f4fd> in the week after the event.\nIf you ha
 ve any questions\, please reach out to support@ala.org.au<mailto:support@a
 la.org.au>\n\n\n\n________________________________________________________
 ________________________\nMicrosoft Teams meeting\nJoin: https://teams.mic
 rosoft.com/meet/42926604886751?p=85JQtO23Sr47Jyrnx1\nMeeting ID: 429 266 0
